{"word":"καταγελάω","slug":"καταγελάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καταγελάω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>άσομαι</el>) (<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>-γεγέλασμαι</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to laugh at, jeer</i> or <i>mock at</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; also <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to laugh scornfully</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to laugh down, deride</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: —<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be derided</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}